This paper deals with channel access schemes in wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of Markov decision process (MDP) for transmission strategies, which is a common technique in information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also addresses the issue of hidden node collisions, which is a security concern and falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper presents simulation results, which involves the use of multimedia tools (cs.MM) for data visualization and analysis.
